Introduction

Seola is a South Korean singer and actress under Starship Entertainment. She is a member of the girl group WJSN (also known as Cosmic Girls), and it's sub-unit WJSN THE BLACK.

She made her debut as part of WJSN under Starship Entertainment and Yuehua Entertainment on February 25, 2016, with the release of their first mini-album "Would You Like?", representing the zodiac sign Sagittarius in the group's concept.

In August 2016, Seola, with fellow members Exy, Soobin, Eunseo, Cheng Xiao, Yeoreum, and Dayoung, collaborated with labelmates MONSTA X to create the sub-unit Y-Teen.

She debuted as an actress in 2017 with the short web-series 'Good Morning Double-Decker Bus', which was used to promote Gyeonggi-do Tourism. Since then, she continued her acting career with leading roles in dramas such as 'In-Out Sider' in 2019, 'Goedam' in 2020, and 'Love in Black Hole' in 2021.

In 2018, Seola took part in the collaboration group WJMK, aiming to bring together two members of WJSN (her and Luda) and two members of Weki Meki (Yoojung and Doyeon), to release a song. Their single, 'Strong', was released on June 1, 2018.

On May 12, 2021, she debuted as a member of WJSN's second sub-unit, WJSN THE BLACK, with the release of the single album "My Attitude".

On March 3, 2023, Starship Entertainment announced that Seola was one of the members who renewed her contract with the agency.

Seola debuted as a soloist with the release of the mini album "Inside Out" on January 23, 2024.
